Michaels Stores December Sales
For all of December 1990, Michaels reported five-week
sales of $66.7 million. It said it used a comparable
four-week period to measure that report against this year's
results.
   For the first 47 weeks of the fiscal year, Michaels said
sales increased 16% to $380.3 million from $328.9 million.
Sales at stores open more than a year rose 9.3% for the first
11 months of the year.